Oppiani- cus engaged the services of one Fabricius, who employed his freed man Scamander for the purpose of poisoning Cluentius. Atthis time Cluentius was ill, and was attended hya physician whose name 'was Cleophantus. The plan was to induce Diogenes, the slave of this' , Cleophantus, to administer the poison.
